1. To view what's written in a file.
Use cat <filename>

2. To change the access permissions of files.
chmod <permission code> <filename>

3. To check which commands you have run till now.
history

4. To remove a directory/Folder.
rm -r <Directory name>  #This will remove the files/directories recursively inside the Directory.

5. To create a fruits.txt file and to view the content.
touch fruits.txt     #To create fruits.txt
cat fruits.txt       #To view the content of fruits.txt


6. Add content in fruits.txt (One in each line) - Apple, Mango, Banana, Cherry, Kiwi, Orange, Guava.
vi fruits.txt
Apple
Mango
Banana
Cherry
Kiwi
Orange
Guava


7. To Show only top three fruits from the file.
cat fruits.txt | head -3
or
head -3 fruits.txt


8. To Show only bottom three fruits from the file.
cat fruits.txt | tail -3
or
tail -3 fruits.txt


9. To create another file colors.txt and to view the content.
touch colors.txt
cat colors.txt


10. Add content in colors.txt (One in each line) - Red, Pink, White, Black, Blue, Orange, Purple, Grey.
cat colors.txt
Red
Pink
White
Black
Blue
Orange
Purple
Grey


11. To find the difference between fruits.txt and Colors.txt file.
diff fruits.txt colors.txt

1,5c1,5
< Apple
< Mango
< Banana
< Cherry
< Kiwi
---
> Red
> Pink
> White
> Black
> Blue
7c7,8
< Guava
---
> Purple
> Grey
